      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Subway Series, Dream and Nightmare</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>David Abramowicz letter on prospects of subway World Series between New York Yankees and New York Mets</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Quaking at the Thought of a Subway Series'' (news article, Oct. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Quaking at the Thought of a Subway Series'' (news article, Oct. 15):</p>
        <p>As a devoted Mets fan, I can relate to New Yorkers who are rooting against a Subway Series because they are worried about the consequences they would endure if their team lost.</p>
        <p>But I have another, darker fear about the potential matchup between the Mets and the Yankees. I have always fantasized about the Mets beating the Yankees in the World Series. If my dream is realized, what will I have left to look forward to?</p>
        <p>DAVID ABRAMOWICZ  Amherst, Mass., Oct. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
